title: Report: Cats' Smith to miss season with injury
text:
Report: Cats' Smith to miss season with injury - Tucson News Now Member Center: Report: Cats' Smith to miss season with injury Posted: TUCSON, AZ (Tucson News Now) - 
The first blow has been leveled at the 2015-2016 Arizona Wildcats Basketball season. 
Scout.com reported Friday night that freshman forward Ray Smith will miss the upcoming season after tearing the ACL in his right knee. 
It’s the second ACL injury in the last year and a half for the talented big man. 
Smith tore his left ACL in the summer of 2014 and did not play his senior season in high school. 
He was expected to make an immediate impact for Sean Miller’s squad.
